5. Information-Theoretic Collapse at Death

Define an information metric I(t), e.g. mutual information between initial state \mathbf{x}(0) and \mathbf{x}(t), or internal memory/entropy.

As t \to T, when V \to 0, we expect:
	â€¢	I(t) \to 0 (memory and structure collapse),
	â€¢	entropy increases or becomes undefined,
	â€¢	control capacity â†’ 0,
	â€¢	adaptive potential â†’ 0.

Thus death as informational collapse â€” not just physical state loss.

