8. Discussion & Implications
	â€¢	Resilience design: For biological or artificial systems, maximizing redundancy, repair dynamics, noise suppression shifts boundary collision far into the future.
	â€¢	Aging as drift: If drift terms or noise amplitude grow over time, hitting time expectation shrinks â€” formalizing aging, degeneration, wear-out.
	â€¢	Ethics of immortality: Attempting to remove absorbing boundary (making \partial\mathcal{M} unreachable) may be logically impossible without infinite redundancy â€” giving mathematical humility to claims of eternal life or perfect immortality.
